----- Original Message -----

> If you have access to a welder, weld a nut to the top of the rounded nut.
> Use a six point socket that will fit the welded on nut and loosen while
the
> nut is still hot.  Works every time and won't harm the redux boxes.

I'll second this method. Works great for removing broken off head studs too!
The heat from welding helps break it loose as well.

